@startuml fig-S15-e3-states
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false

title S15 — Telemetry Validation and Ingestion Pipeline

start

:Receive UDP datagram\non :5515;

:Check IOT1 magic prefix;

if (Valid IOT1 magic?) then (yes)
    :Parse payload\n(sensor_id, seq, value, timestamp);
else (no)
    #FFCDD2:Discard (invalid format);
    :Log: DROPPED (bad magic);
    stop
endif

if (All mandatory fields\npresent?) then (yes)
else (no)
    #FFCDD2:Discard (missing fields);
    :Log: DROPPED (incomplete);
    stop
endif

if (Value in valid range?\n(per-sensor config)) then (yes)
else (out of range)
    #FFCDD2:Discard (out of range);
    :Log: DROPPED (range);
    stop
endif

if (Datagram size ≤ limit?) then (yes)
else (too large)
    #FFCDD2:Discard (oversized);
    stop
endif

:Check deduplication\n(sensor_id + seq);

if (Duplicate?) then (yes)
    #FFF9C4:Discard (already seen);
    stop
else (new)
endif

#C8E6C9:Store in ring buffer\n(sensor_id → latest N readings);

if (Buffer full?) then (yes)
    :Evict oldest reading;
else (no)
endif

:Log: ACCEPTED\n(sensor_id, seq, value);

stop

legend right
  Five validation gates before acceptance:
  1. Magic prefix (IOT1)
  2. Mandatory fields (sensor_id, seq, value)
  3. Value range (configurable per sensor)
  4. Size limit (anti-amplification)
  5. Deduplication (seq already processed)
endlegend
@enduml
